Unix utility 'su'

The Unix utility 'su' is responsible for switching users in the Unix environment.
It can be used to change, for example, to the root user (root), required for various operations
that require high privileges.

USAGE:

su <user>

For more information, enter 'su ?' or 'su --help'.

HISTORY

This command appeared in the Hexagonix H1 (2016-2021).

